<inglise> COUNCIL DECISION of 19 July 1982 on the fixing of rates for the international carriage of goods by rail (82/529/EEC) </inglise>
<eesti> N&Otilde;UKOGU OTSUS 82/529/EM&Uuml; rahvusvahelise raudtee-kaubaveo hindade m&auml;&auml;ramise kohta 19. juuli 1982 </eesti>
<inglise> THE COUNCIL OF THE EUROPEAN COMMUNITIES, </inglise>
<eesti> EUROOPA &Uuml;HENDUSTE N&Otilde;UKOGU, </eesti>
<inglise> Having regard to the Treaty establishing the European Economic Community, and in particular Article 75 thereof, </inglise>
<eesti> v&otilde;ttes arvesse Euroopa Majandus&uuml;henduse asutamislepingut, eriti selle artiklit 75, </eesti>
<inglise> Having regard to the proposal from the Commission, </inglise>
<eesti> v&otilde;ttes arvesse komisjoni ettepanekut, </eesti>
<inglise> Having regard to the opinion of the European Parliament (1), </inglise>
<eesti> v&otilde;ttes arvesse Euroopa Parlamendi arvamust (1) </eesti>
<inglise> Having regard to the opinion of the Economic and Social Committee (2), </inglise>
<eesti> v&otilde;ttes arvesse majandus- ja sotsiaalkomitee arvamust, (2) ning arvestades, et: </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas, pursuant to Council Decision 75/327/EEC of 20 May 1975 on the improvement of the situation of railway undertakings and the harmonization of rules governing financial relations between such undertakings and States (3), railway undertakings should be managed in accordance with economic principles and to this end determine their transport rates with the aim of achieving optimum financial results and financial balance; </inglise>
<eesti> vastavalt n&otilde;ukogu 20. mai 1975. aasta otsusele 75/327/EM&Uuml; (raudtee-ettev&otilde;tjate olukorra parandamise ning selliste ettev&otilde;tjate ja riikide vahelisi finantssuhteid reguleerivate eeskirjade &uuml;htlustamise kohta) (3) tuleks raudtee-ettev&otilde;tjaid majandada koosk&otilde;las majanduslike p&otilde;him&otilde;tetega ja seep&auml;rast peaksid nad kindlaks m&auml;&auml;rama oma veohinnad, et saavutada parimaid v&otilde;imalikke majandustulemusi ja majanduslikku tasakaalu; </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas the attainment of these objectives presupposes the principle of commercial management of the carriage of goods by rail within a framework of sufficient commercial independence; </inglise>
<eesti> nende eesm&auml;rkide saavutamise eelduseks on kaupade raudteeveo &auml;rilise majandamise p&otilde;him&otilde;tete t&auml;itmine piisava &auml;rilise s&otilde;ltumatuse tingimustes; </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas, as part of such commercial management, the rates and conditions for the international carriage of goods between Member States must be laid down by the railway undertakings themselves in accordance with their commercial interests and taking account of the cost price and the market situation; </inglise>
<eesti> sellise &auml;rilise majandamise osana peavad raudtee-ettev&otilde;tjad ise n&auml;gema ette liikmesriikidevahelise rahvusvahelise kaubaveo hinnad ja tingimused koosk&otilde;las oma &auml;rialaste huvidega ning v&otilde;ttes arvesse omahinda ja turuolukorda; </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas the possibility of establishing, by means of bilateral or multilateral agreements between railway undertakings, tariffs with common scales, distinct from national tariffs, offering rates for whole journeys is likely to strengthen the competitive position of railways and to increase the attractiveness of railway services to the customer; </inglise>
<eesti> v&otilde;imalus kehtestada raudtee-ettev&otilde;tjate vaheliste kahe- ja mitmepoolsete kokkulepete abil riiklikest tariifidest erinevad &uuml;histel hinnagraafikutel p&otilde;hinevad tariifid, mis m&auml;&auml;ravad hinna kogu reisiks, tugevdab t&otilde;en&auml;oliselt raudteede konkurentsiv&otilde;imet ja suurendab raudteeteenuste atraktiivsust klientidele; </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas railways must have sufficient commercial independence for intensifying their cooperation in the pursuit of common objectives as regards the fixing of rates and conditions of carriage, </inglise>
<eesti> raudteed peavad olema &auml;riliselt piisavalt s&otilde;ltumatud, et tugevdada oma koost&ouml;&ouml;d &uuml;histe eesm&auml;rkide taotlemisel veohindade ja -tingimuste m&auml;&auml;ramise osas, </eesti>
<inglise> HAS ADOPTED THIS DECISION: </inglise>
<eesti> ON VASTU V&Otilde;TNUD K&Auml;ESOLEVA OTSUSE. </eesti>
<inglise> Article 1 </inglise>
<eesti> Artikkel 1 </eesti>
<inglise> 2. </inglise>
<eesti> 2. </eesti>
<inglise> As regards the Soci&eacute;t&eacute; nationale des chemins de fer luxembourgeois (CFL), Belgium and France shall, in conjunction with Luxembourg, make any amendments to the basic texts which may prove necessary to permit the application of this Decision. </inglise>
<eesti> Soci&eacute;t&eacute; nationale des chemin de fer luxembourgeois' (CFL) suhtes teevad Belgia ja Prantsusmaa koost&ouml;&ouml;s Luksemburgiga asjaomastes &otilde;igusaktides vajalikud muudatused k&auml;esoleva otsuse kohaldamiseks. </eesti>
<inglise> This Decision shall be applied without prejudice to Article 5 of the Belgo-Franco-Luxembourg Convention of 17 April 1946. </inglise>
<eesti> K&auml;esolevat otsust kohaldatakse, ilma et see piiraks 17. aprilli 1946. aasta Belgia-Prantsusmaa-Luksemburgi konventsiooni artikli 5 kohaldamist. </eesti>
<inglise> Article 2 </inglise>
<eesti> Artikkel 2 </eesti>
<inglise> Within the framework of the Community rules applicable and in particular of Article 9 (1) of Council Decision 75/327/EEC, the railway undertakings shall, in accordance with their commercial interests and taking account of costs and the market situation, fix the rates and conditions for the international carriage of goods between Member States. </inglise>
<eesti> Kehtivate &uuml;henduse eeskirjade, eriti n&otilde;ukogu otsuse 75/327/EM&Uuml; artikli 9 l&otilde;ike 1 kohaselt m&auml;&auml;ravad raudtee-ettev&otilde;tjad kindlaks liikmesriikidevahelise rahvusvahelise kaubaveo hinnad ja tingimused koosk&otilde;las oma &auml;rialaste huvidega ning v&otilde;ttes arvesse kulusid ja turuolukorda. </eesti>
<inglise> These rates shall be drawn up in the form of company tariffs or special agreements as provided for in this Decision. </inglise>
<eesti> Need hinnad kehtestatakse k&auml;esoleva otsusega etten&auml;htud ettev&otilde;tjatariifide v&otilde;i erikokkulepete kujul. </eesti>
<inglise> Article 3 </inglise>
<eesti> Artikkel 3 </eesti>
<inglise> 1. </inglise>
<eesti> 1. </eesti>
<inglise> The company tariffs shall be offers to customers. </inglise>
<eesti> Ettev&otilde;tjatariifid on pakkumised klientidele. </eesti>
<inglise> They may be general tariffs or special tariffs and may be differentiated in the light of the special nature of various transport services. </inglise>
<eesti> Need v&otilde;ivad olla &uuml;ld- v&otilde;i eritariifid ja neid v&otilde;ib diferentseerida, v&otilde;ttes arvesse eri veoteenuste laadi. </eesti>
<inglise> 2. </inglise>
<eesti> 2. </eesti>
<inglise> The company tariffs may be established in the form of common tariff scales offering rates for the whole journey, or, where applicable, in the form of tariffs consisting of the sum of the rates obtained from the scales applicable on the sections of the railway networks concerned. </inglise>
<eesti> Ettev&otilde;tjatariifid v&otilde;ib kehtestada &uuml;hisel hinnagraafikul p&otilde;hinevate tariifide kujul, mis m&auml;&auml;ravad hinna kogu reisiks, v&otilde;i v&otilde;imaluse korral tariifide kujul, mis koosnevad asjaomaste raudteev&otilde;rkude eri osades kohaldatavate graafikute p&otilde;hjal saadud hindadest. </eesti>
<inglise> 3. </inglise>
<eesti> 3. </eesti>
<inglise> The company tariffs shall be drawn up in such a way as to ensure the best overall remuneration for the services in view of the market situation and to optimize the financial results of the railway undertakings. </inglise>
<eesti> Ettev&otilde;tjatariifid kehtestatakse nii, et need turuolukorda arvesse v&otilde;ttes tagaksid parima tasu teenuste eest ja kindlustaksid raudtee-ettev&otilde;tjatele parimad v&otilde;imalikud majandustulemused. </eesti>
<inglise> Article 4 </inglise>
<eesti> Artikkel 4 </eesti>
<inglise> In so far as the railway undertakings, taking account of market requirements and their own interests, establish tariffs with common scales offering rates for whole journeys, the rates set out in those tariffs may be independent of those obtained by adding the rates of the national tariffs. </inglise>
<eesti> Kui raudtee-ettev&otilde;tjad, arvestades turun&otilde;udeid ja oma huve, kehtestavad tariifid &uuml;histe hinnagraafikute p&otilde;hjal, m&auml;&auml;rates hinna kogu reisiks, v&otilde;ivad nende tariifidega kehtestatud hinnad olla s&otilde;ltumatud riiklikele tariifidele vastavate hindade summast. </eesti>
<inglise> These tariffs shall be drawn up, modified or withdrawn by bilateral or multilateral agreements between the railway undertakings. </inglise>
<eesti> Need tariifid kehtestatakse, neid muudetakse v&otilde;i need t&uuml;histatakse raudtee-ettev&otilde;tjate vaheliste kahe-v&otilde;i mitmepoolsete kokkulepetega. </eesti>
<inglise> Article 5 </inglise>
<eesti> Artikkel 5 </eesti>
<inglise> The railway undertakings shall have the commercial independence necessary for intensifying their cooperation in the quotation of transport rates and conditions for international transport in order to pursue common objectives, in particular as regards the creation of revenue pools and the delegation of powers between railway undertakings for the conclusion of special agreements with customers. </inglise>
<eesti> Raudtee-ettev&otilde;tjad on &auml;riliselt piisavalt s&otilde;ltumatud, et tugevdada oma koost&ouml;&ouml;d rahvusvaheliste vedude veohindade ja -tingimuste m&auml;&auml;ramisel &uuml;histe eesm&auml;rkide taotlemiseks, moodustades tulupuule ja volitades teisi raudtee-ettev&otilde;tjaid erikokkulepete s&otilde;lmimiseks klientidega. </eesti>
<inglise> Article 6 </inglise>
<eesti> Artikkel 6 </eesti>
<inglise> Special agreements may be concluded between the railway undertakings concerned and customers designated by name; they shall contain rates which take account of conditions of a technical and commercial character peculiar to the type of transport involved. </inglise>
<eesti> Erikokkuleppeid v&otilde;ib s&otilde;lmida asjaomaste raudtee-ettev&otilde;tjate ja nimeliselt m&auml;&auml;ratud klientide vahel; kokkulepped sisaldavad hindu, mis v&otilde;tavad arvesse asjaomasele veoliigile iseloomulikke tehnilisi ja &auml;rialaseid tingimusi. </eesti>
<inglise> Article 7 </inglise>
<eesti> Artikkel 7 </eesti>
<inglise> In order to promote the attainment of the objectives set out in Council Decision 75/327/EEC, railway undertakings shall apply rates in international goods traffic between Member States intended to: </inglise>
<eesti> N&otilde;ukogu otsuses 75/327/EM&Uuml; s&auml;testatud eesm&auml;rkide saavutamise soodustamiseks kohaldavad raudtee-ettev&otilde;tjad liikmesriikidevahelise rahvusvahelise kaubaveo suhtes selliseid hindu, mis: </eesti>
<inglise> - ensure that the assignable costs specific to thetraffic concerned by this Decision are covered, </inglise>
<eesti> - tagavad, et kaetakse k&auml;esolevas otsuses k&auml;sitletud veole etten&auml;htud kulud, </eesti>
<inglise> - make a positive contribution to covering jointcosts. </inglise>
<eesti> - aitavad katta &uuml;hiseid kulusid. </eesti>
<inglise> Article 8 </inglise>
<eesti> Artikkel 8 </eesti>
<inglise> Company tariffs shall be published in railway undertakings' tariff notices or by other appropriate means before they are applied; their publication shall be compulsory only in those Member States where the railway undertakings participate in these tariffs as the network of departure or destination. </inglise>
<eesti> Ettev&otilde;tjatariifid avaldatakse enne nende kohaldamist raudtee-ettev&otilde;tjate tariifiteatistes v&otilde;i muul asjakohasel viisil; tariifide avaldamine on kohustuslik ainult nende liikmesriikides, kus raudtee-ettev&otilde;tjad nendes tariifides l&auml;hte- v&otilde;i sihtv&otilde;rguna osalevad. </eesti>
<inglise> Article 9 </inglise>
<eesti> Artikkel 9 </eesti>
<inglise> 1. </inglise>
<eesti> 1. </eesti>
<inglise> Before 1 January 1983 and after consultation with the Commission, the Member States shall adopt the provisions necessary for the implementation of this Decision. </inglise>
<eesti> Enne 1. jaanuari 1983 ja p&auml;rast komisjoniga konsulteerimist v&otilde;tavad liikmesriigid vastu k&auml;esoleva otsuse rakendamiseks vajalikud eeskirjad. </eesti>
<inglise> 2. </inglise>
<eesti> 2. </eesti>
<inglise> At the request of a Member State or if the Commission considers it advisable, the latter shall consult the Member States concerned on the draft provisions referred to in paragraph 1. </inglise>
<eesti> Liikmesriigi taotluse korral v&otilde;i kui komisjon seda soovitavaks peab, konsulteerib komisjon asjaomaste liikmesriikidega l&otilde;ikes 1 nimetatud eeskirjade eeln&otilde;ude osas. </eesti>
<inglise> Article 10 </inglise>
<eesti> Artikkel 10 </eesti>
<inglise> Five years after the entry into force of this Decision, the Commission shall report to the Council on the results of its implementation. </inglise>
<eesti> Viie aasta jooksul alates k&auml;esoleva otsuse j&otilde;ustumisest esitab komisjon n&otilde;ukogule aruande selle rakendamise kohta. </eesti>
<inglise> The Council shall review the situation in the light of this report and, on a proposal from the Commission, shall take the appropriate decision acting by a qualified majority. </inglise>
<eesti> N&otilde;ukogu vaatab aruannet arvesse v&otilde;ttes olukorra &uuml;le ja teeb komisjoni ettepanekul asjakohase otsuse kvalifitseeritud h&auml;&auml;lteenamusega. </eesti>
<inglise> Article 11 </inglise>
<eesti> Artikkel 11 </eesti>
<inglise> This Decision is addressed to the Member States. </inglise>
<eesti> K&auml;esolev otsus on adresseeritud liikmesriikidele. </eesti>
<inglise> Done at Brussels, 19 July 1982. </inglise>
<eesti> Br&uuml;ssel, 19. juuli 1982 </eesti>
<inglise> For the Council </inglise>
